==English==
===Adjective===
'''Misanthropic'''
#Hating or disliking mankind.

====Etymology====
From ''mis'' (not, negative, disliking) + ''anthropic'' (human)

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒpɪk|-ɒpɪk]]

====Antonyms====
*[[philanthropic]] (loving human race)

===See also===
*[[altruism]] (strong like of human race)
*[[misanthropy]] (hatred of human race)
*[[misanthropist]]
*[[misanthrope]]
*[[misandry]] (hatred of males)
*[[misogyny]] (hatred of females)

